FishCrucian.Name: Crucian
FishCrucian.Description: The crucian carp is a medium-sized member of the common carp family Cyprinidae. It occurs widely in northern European regions.

FishWhiteAmur.Name: White Amur
FishWhiteAmur.Description: The grass carp (Ctenopharyngodon idella) is a large herbivorous freshwater fish species of the family Cyprinidae native to eastern Asia.

FishPike.Name: Pike
FishPike.Description: The northern pike, known simply as a pike in Britain, Ireland, most of Canada, and most parts of the United States, is a species of carnivorous fish of the genus Esox. They are typical of brackish and fresh waters of the Northern Hemisphere.

FishIde.Name: Ide
FishIde.Description: The ide (Leuciscus idus), or orfe, is a freshwater fish of the family Cyprinidae found in larger rivers, ponds, and lakes across northern Europe and Asia.

FishPerch.Name: Perch
FishPerch.Description: Perca fluviatilis, is a predatory species of perch found in Europe and northern Asia. The species is a popular quarry for anglers, and has been widely introduced beyond its native area, into Australia, New Zealand, and South Africa.

Lure1.Name: Lure 1
Lure1.Description: Lure 1 is through wired, and feature lifelike gills and a reflective finish. Center weighted (flutter), red 3D eyes, epoxy coated.

Lure2.Name: Lure 2
Lure2.Description: Lure 2 is free style jigs that drop fast with lots of flutter. DEEP FORCE jigs are clear coated for durability. The jigs listed below are rigged with 9/0 heavy duty live bait hooks on Kevlar cord attached to a 300 lb test Owner solid ring.

Lure3.Name: Lure 3
Lure3.Description: The Lure 3 has earned its place in history as the most productive lure ever to come along. Its versatility is unmatched. Ideal for surf-casting and inland bays.

Lure4.Name: Lure 4
Lure4.Description: Large lures catch large fish. Great for close offshore and deeper inland bays.

Lure5.Name: Lure 5
Lure5.Description: Lure 5 is compact top water lures that feature an extra wide mouth which causes a very large splash, drawing fish in from long distances. These lures are perfectly weighted for long distance casting.

Lure6.Name: Lure 6
Lure6.Description: The Lure 6 is versatile top water plugs for all game species. Great for walk the dog, slash, rip and stop, slow or fast retrieve techniques. These lures are precisely weighted for maximum casting distance.

Lure7.Name: Lure 7
Lure7.Description: This flat-sided crankbait has an authentic profile and precise swimming action that is so accurate it is in a league of its own. The internal design of this lure generates a soft roll and tight wiggle action.

Lure8.Name: Lure 8
Lure8.Description: The Lure 8 replicate a juvenile sunfish, pushed to the surface by predatory fish.

Lure9.Name: Lure 9
Lure9.Description: The Lure 9 are individually wrapped for fresh bait every time you rip one open! Slick Sticks have an irresistible soft texture.

Lure10.Name: Lure 10
Lure10.Description: The Lure 10 are made from a soft flexible material that is able to successfully hold scents. This bait won't dry up if they are left out in the sun or air.

Rod1.Name: Rod 1
Rod1.Description: This rods are constructed with powerful, responsive and durable IM-6 graphite. Fast, flexible tips with hook-setting strength to spare, and graphite reel seats.

Rod2.Name: Rod 2
Rod2.Description: This rod are a powerful, durable and reasonably priced model that anglers covet. The model is designed to be pushed to the max and perform perfectly.

Rod3.Name: Rod 3
Rod3.Description: This rod deliver the ultimate in strength, sensitivity, weight, and balance!

Help.Title: Help
Help.Text:
What will be your biggest catch? Find the Perfect Location. Choose the Right Bait. Do not rush to pull the float, patience is a certain guarantee of success. Enjoy the positive peace in this Ice Fishing game. And most importantly fishing, excitement and beauty.

  Instruction:
 - To catch, use the large arrows in the upper right and lower right corners of the screen.
 - In the upper left corner of the screen you will see a warning about the tension of the fishing line. If the tension of the fishing line is strong, then the green color will turn into red. The fishing line may break and you will lose the caught fish.
 - You can change lures, fishing rods, fishing spots.
 - For every caught any fish, you will get money. With this money you can buy new bait, the rods.
